\section{GENERAL}
\subsection{Scope}
This document gives a formal specification of the SSQL semantics. It constitutes deliverable D3 of work package 1a, as given
in section 7 of the Secure Database Technical Proposal, \cite{DS/FMU/017}.

\subsection{Introduction}
In the introduction to \cite{DS/FMU/FEF/004} we stated the intention
to present the formalisation of the semantics of
SSQL in three main parts. The functions $hide$ and $updateState$
are formalised in \cite{DS/FMU/FEF/004}; the remaining part of
the formalisation of SSQL is given in this document. It consists of the main functionality of SSQL, i.e. how the 
result of a query is computed from the state of the database.

